   - nxrsecrypt command overview -

   commands are split by ' // ' so for instance, in the command 'a // x // y // z'
   'a' is the command, 'x' is argument 1, 'y' is argument 2, 'z' is argument 3

   -basic functionality-
   exit - exit nxrsecrypt
   clear - clear the screen (header remains)
   restart - restart nxrsecrypt
   info - display software info

   -encryption-
   encrypt // <encryption mapping> // <text> - encrypt text
   decrypt // <encryption mapping> // <text> - decrypt text

   -encryption mapping-
   list-em - list encryption maps
   gen-em // <map name> // <chunk length> // <character list> - generate an encryption map (the last argument is optional, as it defaults to 'default')
   get-em // <encryption mapping name> - display an encryption map
   del-em // <encryption mapping name> - delete an encryption map
   
   list-cl - list encryption mapping character lists
   create-cl // <list name> // <characters> - create a character list
   del-cl // <character list name> - delete a character list
   get-cl // <character list name> - display a character list 

   -dev commands-
   reset - reset encryption mappings folder, char lists, config, and treats the user as new
   reset-config - reset config to default config
   load-config - copy the user config file to the actual config module
   get-config - display the current config
   set-config // <variable> // <new value> - change the value of a variable in the config
   update - pull the lastest changes from the github repo

   check the README.md for more detailed documentation :)
